summary: This document appears to be a set of instructions for witnesses regarding the identification of individuals in photographs related to a case. It emphasizes the importance of not jumping to conclusions and ensuring that innocent individuals are not wrongly identified. The document includes procedural notes for officers involved in the case.
keyFacts: Witnesses are instructed not to conclude or guess that the photographs contain the picture of the person who committed the crime.
Witnesses are not obliged to identify anyone and should focus on freeing innocent persons from suspicion.
Witnesses are advised not to discuss the case with other witnesses.
